data.message: I use an extension called one tab to save my sessions for later browsing.

Thanks all. In not as much concerned with solving this (currently I set Chrome to open new tab on start to force my self to make a decision about tabs).

I'm more interested in whether it's a common issue or a corrupted set of settings or maybe impact of some extension. 

I've had an issue before where syncing your profile would restore a bad profile to a fresh computer when you login with wasn't account, so, even that I reinstalled Windows recently (after a year or more of last install, unrelated to this), I can't be 100% sure it's not just my profile.

I might just try another profile and see if it still happens.
I have suffered from this issue few months ago and Chrome was closed due to an error. Later on I didn't face this error again
